column12: Flight status signal providing device for e.g. aircraft, has threshold units for setting aircraft speed statuses, where device computes flight status signal based on aircraft speed signals and engine status signals
column13: The device (1) has threshold units (31-33) for setting aircraft speed statuses (S1'-S3') in a positive logical level on an output side when aircraft speed signals (S1-S3) are greater than a preset threshold, where the device computes a flight status signal (FS) based on the signals (S1-S3), engine status signals (S4-S7), evacuation signals (S8-S10), front engine status signals (S11, S12) and main gear status signals (S13-S16). The device receives the signals via a bus e.g. Avionics full duplex switched Ethernetbus. Independent claims are also included for the following: (1) a system comprising a bus for transmitting an aircraft speed signal (2) a method for providing a flight status signal for an aircraft (3) a method for generating a door closing signal for locking a door of an aircraft.

column12: Vorrichtung und Verfahren zum Bereitstellen eines Flugstatussignals
column13: Vorrichtung (1) zum Bereitstellen eines Flugstatussignals (FS) für ein Flugzeug, welches angibt, ob das Flugzeug in der Luft oder am Boden ist, wobei die Vorrichtung (1) das Flugstatussignal (FS) in Abhängigkeit einer Anzahl N1 unterschiedlich bereitgestellter Fluggeschwindigkeitssignale (S1-S3), einer Anzahl N2 unterschiedlich bereitgestellter Triebwerksstatussignale (S4-S7), einer Anzahl N4 unterschiedlich bereitgestellter Evakuierungssignale (S8-S10), einer Anzahl N3 unterschiedlich bereitgestellter Frontfahrwerksstatussignale (S11, S12) und einer Anzahl N5 unterschiedlich bereitgestellter Hauptfahrwerksstatussignale (S13-S16) berechnet.

column12: Device And Method For Providing A Flight Status Signal
column13: The present invention provides a device for providing an aircraft flight status signal which indicates whether the aircraft is in the air or on the ground, which device calculates the flight status signal as a function of a number of differently provided flight speed signals, a number of differently provided engine status signals, a number of differently provided evacuation signals, a number of differently provided front undercarriage status signals and a number of differently provided main undercarriage status signals.
